Network engineer and project manager - IPTV, Internet video and Virtual worlds, 
Research & Development, Orange Lab San Francisco 

• Recommend Orange with innovative and disruptive network architectures and technologies, especially in the area of IP Television (IPTV), Internet videos services and virtual worlds; 
• Scout for new services and products and work closely with vendors to evaluate their networking products in Lab; 
• Lead projects related to Internet video and virtual worlds; 
• Analyze trends in North American's Market for technology transfer or potential US Market opportunities for Orange; 
• Propose innovative services that can be delivered over Orange’s existing IPTV and Internet video offerings (through best practices, white papers, proof of concept and prototypes); 
• Other projects are related to: 
-- Online multiplayer video games and the impact on the Network; 
-- Carrier SOA: conduct an anticipation study in the field of XML Networking and implemented a demo leveraging XML routing technology; 
-- Network-based security solutions

Specialties:
Technical skills: 
-- Network Computing – IPTV and Internet video distribution architectures, online gaming, XML networking, traffic shaping, network-based security; 
-- Programming – XML language (Web Services), SQL, XQuery, Java, HTML
